		<body>
			<pb n="1R"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>New Orleans</placeName> <date>March 18th<add>&#63;</add> 1854</date></p>
				<p><addressee>Revd Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">Dr Sir</p>
				<p>I am happy to inform you the Brig <add>&#63;</add><lb/> Mallory has duly arrived &#38; one case now<lb/> in store  I am busy <sic>makeing</sic> out the lists<lb/> of the respective names &#38; the books to be sent<lb/> them &#38; at same time informing them of the<lb/> Books being now ready for delivery &#38; shall<lb/> also as soon as the other case comes up<lb/> endeavour forwarding to <persName>Mr Osterman</persName><lb/> the Books named.  <persName>John Marks</persName> now resides<lb/> in <placeName>New York</placeName>  <persName>M. Barnett</persName> is residing in<lb/> <placeName>San Francisco</placeName> &#40;<persName>Hirshfield</persName> in <placeName>New York</placeName><lb/> is his Partner&#41; <persName>Elias Newburger</persName> is<lb/> yet here but also about leaving &#38; I doubt<lb/> if he is <hi rend="underline">that Be<add>&#63;</add></hi> to take the work he <sic>orderd</sic><lb/>  I shall however try him <persName>Dr I L Craucow<add>&#63;</add></persName> I<lb/> think will take the Books &#38; <persName>Rodriguez </persName>also<lb/> I will do all I can do &#38; as soon as I<lb/> obtain any funds send it to you</p>
				<p>The Hebrew Ball of the Hebrew Benevolent<lb/> association came off last night it was a<lb/> brilliant affair well attended  I have no<lb/> Doubt a Handsome sum will have been<lb/> made.  My time is at the disposal of another &#38; of course<lb/> I cannot devote that time to private correspondence</p>
			<pb n="1V"/>
				<p>that I could wish still I shall strive not<lb/> to neglect your Interest if I neglect<lb/> all others</p>
			<p rend="indent(7)">Yours Very Truly</p>
			<p rend="indent(7)"><persName role="author">Isaac Hart</persName></p>
				<p>I am sorry you did not have any name or<lb/> one of the Handsome Bibles.</p>
				<p>I must not omit to congratulate you on<lb/> the style &#38; finish of this book.  It could<lb/> not be excell&#39;d &#38; is sure to please</p>
		</body>
